<section id="sourdough-secrets" class="p-6 bg-[#f8f8f8] text-[#333]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">Sourdough Secrets</h2>
        <p>
            Sourdough is not just bread; it's a time-honored craft that blends science and artistry. The magic of sourdough lies in its unique fermentation process, which uses naturally occurring wild yeast and lactic acid bacteria from the environment to leaven the dough. This symbiotic relationship creates a tangy flavor profile and a chewy texture that distinguishes sourdough from commercial yeasted bread. The key to mastering sourdough lies in understanding the importance of a healthy starter, proper hydration, and patience during fermentation and proofing. Each bake can vary based on factors such as temperature, humidity, and flour type, making sourdough baking both a delightful challenge and an opportunity for creativity. Whether you're experimenting with different flours or adjusting hydration levels, the secrets of sourdough offer a rewarding journey that connects bakers to centuries of tradition and a community of enthusiasts eager to share their knowledge and tips.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
